HEADWORD: Syncategorematic
<hw>Syn*cat`e*gor`e*mat"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<?/; <grk>sy`n</grk> with + <?/ a predicate. See <er>Syn-</er>, and
<er>Categorematic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Logic)</fld> <def>Not capable of
being used as a term by itself; -- said of words, as an adverb or
preposition.</def>⟦br⟧
